### Page 350: About the Author

- **Robert L. Heilbroner** began studying great economists at
  **Harvard University** in 1936; graduated summa cum laude, Phi Beta Kappa
- Practiced economics in government and business before completing
  graduate work at the **New School for Social Research**
- *The Worldly Philosophers* (first published **1953**) was an immediate
  success; translated into **three dozen languages**; became a standard
  introductory economics text at colleges worldwide
- Also authored *Twenty-First Century Capitalism* and *Visions of the Future*
- Held the **Norman Thomas Professor of Economics** chair at the New School
- Vice president of the **American Economic Association**; nominated
  Scholar of the Year by the New York State Council of the Humanities

### Page 351: Title Page

- Full title: *The Worldly Philosophers: The Lives, Times, and Ideas
